The paper discusses the challenges of designing static analyses for dynamic languages and proposes a new approach called "abstracting abstract machines" (AAM) to address these challenges. This approach is specifically targeted towards programming language (cs.PL) analysis and software engineering (cs.SE) applications. The paper also mentions the use of memoization, which is a technique commonly used in logic and verification (cs.LO) and formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing automata theoretic models, which is a topic relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
